amarantin
=========

`amarantin` is a small C++/ROOT utility library plus one CLI for building
ROOT sample containers from text lists of input ROOT files.

Supported workflow
------------------

The supported path in this repository is:

1. Build file lists with [`tools/mklist.sh`](/Users/user/programs/amarantin/tools/mklist.sh).
2. Build the library and CLI with `make`.
3. Run `build/bin/mk_sample` to produce a sample ROOT file.

The `io` library contains the main logic. The `app` layer is intentionally thin.

Build
-----

This repository expects a ROOT-enabled environment. On UBOONE-style systems,
that usually means sourcing [`.setup.sh`](/Users/user/programs/amarantin/.setup.sh)
first.

Build everything:

```bash
make
```

Build only the sample CLI:

```bash
make -C app BUILD_DIR=../build all
```

Create input lists
------------------

Generate a sorted `.list` file of ROOT files from a directory:

```bash
tools/mklist.sh \
  --dir /path/to/ntuples \
  --pat "nu_selection.root,nu_selection_data.root" \
  --out samplelists/run1/beam-s0.list
```

Build a sample container
------------------------

Basic usage:

```bash
build/bin/mk_sample output.root input.list [origin] [variation] [beam] [polarity]
```

The CLI also supports an explicit run database path:

```bash
build/bin/mk_sample \
  --run-db /path/to/run.db \
  build/samples/run1/beam-s0.root \
  samplelists/run1/beam-s0.list \
  data nominal numi fhc
```

If `--run-db` is not provided, the library uses:

1. `AMARANTIN_RUN_DB` if it is set.
2. `/exp/uboone/data/uboonebeam/beamdb/run.db` otherwise.

Concepts
--------

`sample`
  A ROOT container produced by `mk_sample`. It stores sample metadata, summed
  exposure values, and per-partition provenance.

`partition`
  One entry from the top-level input list. Each partition points to a text file
  containing ROOT file paths.

`provenance`
  The scanned metadata for a partition: source ROOT files, unique `(run, subrun)`
  pairs, POT sum from the input `SubRun` trees, and entry counts.

Repository layout
-----------------

[`io/include/SampleIO.hh`](/Users/user/programs/amarantin/io/include/SampleIO.hh)
  Main supported API for building and reading sample ROOT files.

[`io/src/ArtProvenanceIO.cc`](/Users/user/programs/amarantin/io/src/ArtProvenanceIO.cc)
  Scans ROOT files, finds `SubRun` trees, and extracts run/subrun and POT data.

[`io/src/RunDatabaseService.cc`](/Users/user/programs/amarantin/io/src/RunDatabaseService.cc)
  Reads beam exposure summaries from SQLite for a set of run/subrun pairs.

[`app/mk_sample.cc`](/Users/user/programs/amarantin/app/mk_sample.cc)
  Thin CLI around `SampleIO`.

[`samples-dag.mk`](/Users/user/programs/amarantin/samples-dag.mk)
  Make-based batch workflow for generating many list files and sample outputs.

Notes on the codebase
---------------------

`SampleIO` is the current supported container path.

`DatasetIO` is a more general multi-sample container abstraction that exists in
the tree but is not yet the main write path used by the CLI.

`EventListIO` is only a stub at the moment.
